### Hop In — REST API test collection
### Use with VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client)
### Run requests in order: auth → trips → bookings → ratings → notifications → admin
### After login, copy the token into @driverToken / @passengerToken / @adminToken

@host = http://localhost:5000
@contentType = application/json

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HEALTH
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### GET /api/health
GET {{host}}/api/health

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTH
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register driver — VALID
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "full_name": "Albert Kola",
  "email": "albert@test.com",
  "phone": "+355691111111",
  "password": "hopin12345",
  "role": "driver"
}

### Register passenger — VALID
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "full_name": "Roena Vrana",
  "email": "roena@test.com",
  "phone": "+355692222222",
  "password": "hopin12345",
  "role": "passenger"
}

### Register — INVALID (missing fields, short password, bad role)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "bad",
  "password": "123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### Register — INVALID (duplicate email → 409)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "full_name": "Dup",
  "email": "albert@test.com",
  "phone": "+355690000000",
  "password": "hopin12345",
  "role": "driver"
}

### Login driver
# @name loginDriver
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "albert@test.com",
  "password": "hopin12345"
}

###
@driverToken = {{loginDriver.response.body.data.token}}

### Login passenger
# @name loginPassenger
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "roena@test.com",
  "password": "hopin12345"
}

###
@passengerToken = {{loginPassenger.response.body.data.token}}

### Login — INVALID (wrong password)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "email": "albert@test.com", "password": "wrongpass" }

### Login — INVALID (unknown email)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "email": "noone@nowhere.com", "password": "whatever1" }

### Logout — no token (401)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/logout

### Logout — with token
POST {{host}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

